12	pleasanton-garage	Pleasanton Garage	Pleasanton	Garage Remodel	2025	The detached garage of our Pleasanton Modern Farmhouse — stripped of its stucco and rebuilt inside and out with reclaimed wood siding, a workshop, bathroom, and traditional barn sconces.	\N	\N	/assets/images-opt/ff5b18_042b3d66e8904b4188c0ec509b2595d6_mv2.webp	{/assets/images-opt/ff5b18_dab676506e77455e942b02a857f21cc3_mv2.webp,/assets/images-opt/ff5b18_f8bf8933487f45db825a713b4ea4c540_mv2.webp,/assets/images-opt/ff5b18_5f016abc7ce04830a7f65e61c2b4a3fa_mv2.webp,/assets/images-opt/ff5b18_fa6237e022fb42d5812a4e932b054bee_mv2.webp,/assets/images-opt/ff5b18_e9017ba51d1544b789d5add8c4ecc484_mv2.webp,/assets/images-opt/ff5b18_042b3d66e8904b4188c0ec509b2595d6_mv2.webp}	t	12	2026-03-31 02:25:34.606122+00	2026-04-04 05:03:29.578533+00	CA	garage-specialty	The detached garage of our Pleasanton Modern Farmhouse — stripped of its stucco and rebuilt inside and out with reclaimed wood siding, a workshop, bathroom, and traditional barn sconces.	Our clients from the Pleasanton Modern Farmhouse had a detached garage that had been plastered with stucco by a previous property owner. They had a vision to remodel the garage inside and out to better fit their family's needs and to blend in with the surrounding property.\n\nThe new interior includes a bathroom, a workshop space and a traditional double carport. The exterior is re-clad with reclaimed wood on the siding and new garage doors. A metal roll up door on the backside lets fresh air into the workshop.\n\nTraditional barn sconces flank the doors to make this structure look more like an original barn than a garage — blending seamlessly with the farmhouse character of the main property.	{"What":"Garage Remodel","Where":"Pleasanton, CA","When":"2025"}	ff5b18_042b3d66e8904b4188c0ec509b2595d6_mv2	jpg	[["ff5b18_dab676506e77455e942b02a857f21cc3_mv2", "jpg"], ["ff5b18_f8bf8933487f45db825a713b4ea4c540_mv2", "jpg"], ["ff5b18_5f016abc7ce04830a7f65e61c2b4a3fa_mv2", "jpg"], ["