1	daily	2026-03-19	2026-03-19	Daily Performance Report — 2026-03-19	\N	## Daily Performance Report — March 19, 2026\n\n---\n\n### Executive Summary\n\nThursday, March 19 is a scheduled **non-active ad day** for Ridgecrest Designs, and campaigns ran as intended — no impressions, clicks, or spend were recorded. The $125.00 daily budget remains fully intact. No anomalies or optimization actions were triggered today.\n\n---\n\n### Key Metrics\n\n| Impressions | Clicks | Conversions | Spend | Avg CPC | CPL |\n|:-----------:|:------:|:-----------:|:-----:|:-------:|:---:|\n| 0 | 0 | 0 | $0.00 | $0.00 | — |\n\n---\n\n### Campaign Breakdown\n\n| Campaign | Impressions | Clicks | Conversions | Spend | CTR | CPL |\n|----------|:-----------:|:------:|:-----------:|:-----:|:---:|:---:|\n| — | — | — | — | — | — | — |\n\n> ℹ️ No campaigns were active today. This is expected behavior for a non-active scheduled day.\n\n---\n\n### Budget Status\n\n- **Daily cap:** $125.00\n- **Today's spend:** $0.00\n- **Remaining:** $125.00\n- **Pacing:** Under *(non-active day — expected)*\n- **Is today an active ad day?** No\n\n---\n\n### Optimizations Applied\n\n> No optimization actions were applied today. Campaigns were paused per the active-day schedule.\n\n---\n\n### Alerts & Flags\n\n> ✅ No alerts or flags. Zero spend on a non-active day is consistent with the configured schedule. No CPL violations, budget overruns, or anomalies to report.\n\n---\n\n### Recommendations\n\n1. **Confirm tomorrow's schedule is active and budgeted correctly.** Verify that Friday, March 20 is flagged as an active day and that the $125.00 daily cap is properly applied before campaigns go live in the morning window.\n\n2. **Review creative and bid strategy ahead of the weekend.** Affluent East Bay homeowners are more likely to engage with premium home renovation content Friday through Sunday. Ensure top-performing ad copy and extensions are prioritized for the next active cycle.\n\n3. **Audit audience targeting se